-- Itau Lures Corcoran From UBS to Head International Bond Syndication Group
-- B y   D r e w   B e n s o n
-- 2012-02-23T18:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/itau-lures-corcoran-from-ubs-to-head-bond-syndication-group.html
Itau Unibanco Holding SA (ITUB4) , Latin
America’s biggest bank by market value, hired John Corcoran from
UBS AG to lead the lender’s international bond syndication group
in New York.  Corcoran, who replaces Surat Maheshwari, will start in mid-
March, said Douglas Chen, head of international fixed-income
distribution at Itau.  UBS spokesman Christiaan Brakman confirmed Corcoran left
the Zurich-based bank, where he was a managing director in debt
capital markets syndication in Stamford, Connecticut.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Drew Benson in  Buenos Aires  at 
